Then maybe your subs have literally left you. Last thing you could do is try posting one video per day hoping they will remember you and restart following your channel. But you could as well use the experience you got from this channel to build a new one, this time, it should be more focused and has more related videos from the beginning. In that way people can expect more on the topic and be more likely to come back.

Have you done the necessary things to consider Youtube as a career path. These are: Dedication, investment, study. In order for it to be a career, it has to be a viable business, therefore you should study what a viable business is and consider it as such from the beginning. It might still not work and backfire later on, but you need to have the necessary strength to accept your mistakes and keep working hard. Even with all the effort you make it can still not succeed, but that's what risk is and "who risks nothing gets nothing" .... On the other hand, you could just relax, post one or two videos here and there from time to time, and bet on their quality, i.e. gamble on getting a miracle hit....but that's not an effective way of making a career.
